summary:
The Security Council,

Welcoming the Secretary-General's report on the UN operation in Cyprus, 
calls on parties to urgently address the humanitarian issue of missing persons,

Noting the Government of Cyprus's agreement to extend the UN Peacekeeping Force in Cyprus (UNFICYP) due to prevailing conditions,

Reaffirms its relevant resolutions on Cyprus, particularly resolution 1251 (1999);

Decides to extend UNFICYP's mandate until 15 December 2002;

Requests a report by 1 December 2002 on the implementation of this resolution;

Urges the Turkish Cypriot side and Turkish forces to lift restrictions on UNFICYP operations and restore the military status quo ante of Strovilia;

Decides to remain seized of the matter.
